<subSubSection lastPageId="45" lastPageNumber="46" pageId="44" pageNumber="45" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="44.[151,1436,1701,2014]" box="[199,1436,1989,2014]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,1989,2014]" pageId="44" pageNumber="45">DISCUSSION:</emphasis>
Full descriptions, illustrations, and an identification key to adults can be found in Zwick and
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="45.[151,1435,151,212]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Surenkholoo (2005). Nymphs of all species in the eastern Palearctic have been described by Teslenko and Zhiltzova (2006), with an accompanying species-level identification key, primarily using coloration patterns.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
